00/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%2052%2052'%3E%3C/svg%3E" data-lazy-srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/21592cbe5834ed3ee55ead5533bf7d63ea19a69e91eb55e61b9c4454a7c20f87?s=104&#038;d=blank&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-52 photo' height='52' width='52' decoding='async' data-lazy-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/21592cbe5834ed3ee55ead5533bf7d63ea19a69e91eb55e61b9c4454a7c20f87?s=52&#038;d=blank&#038;r=g"/><noscript><img data-pin-nopin="nopin" alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/21592cbe5834ed3ee55ead5533bf7d63ea19a69e91eb55e61b9c4454a7c20f87?s=52&#038;d=blank&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/21592cbe5834ed3ee55ead5533bf7d63ea19a69e91eb55e61b9c4454a7c20f87?s=104&#038;d=blank&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-52 photo' height='52' width='52' decoding='async'/></noscript></a><div class="post-header__info--inner"><span class="entry-author"><a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/about/">Brittany Mullins</a></span><span class="post-date">Updated Feb 25, 2026</span><div class="cwp-recipe-key"><a title="Gluten-Free" href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/category/diet-preference/gluten-free/"><span class="cwp-recipe-key__gf">GF<span class="screen-reader-text">Gluten-Free</span></span></a><a title="High-Protein" href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/category/diet-preference/protein/"><span class="cwp-recipe-key__hp">HP<span class="screen-reader-text">High-Protein</span></span></a></div></div></div><div class="post-header__meta"><a class="wp-element-button cwp-jtr" href="#wprm-recipe-container-143265">Jump to Recipe  ▼</a><p class="post-header__comments"><svg width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" role="img" focusable="false"><use href="#wprm-cwp-chat-2"></use></svg><a href="#comments">55 Comments</a></p><p class="cwp-wprm-servings"><svg width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" role="img" focusable="false"><use href="#wprm-cwp-vegetables-plate"></use></svg>Servings: 8</p><p class="entry-total-time"><svg width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" role="img" focusable="false"><use href="#wprm-cwp-clock-2"></use></svg>45 mins</p></div></div><div class="aff-disc"><p>This post may include <a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/privacy-policy/#advertising">affiliate links</a>. Thank you for your support.</p>
</div><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">

<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p>This delicious chocolate <strong>protein cake</strong> is guaranteed to be your new favorite dessert! It&rsquo;s rich, moist, naturally sweetened and packed with 15 grams of protein per slice.</p>
</blockquote>



<script type="text/rocketlazyloadscript" data-rocket-src="https://cdn.jwplayer.com/v2/sites/4On4mALN/placements/BKZk4H5j/embed.js?custom.BKZk4H5j.media_id=otqfZlyS" data-rocket-defer defer></script>



<div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>If you love chocolate cake but also love sneaking a little extra protein into your day, this one&rsquo;s for you.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143642" data-pin-description="This delicious chocolate protein cake is guaranteed to be your new favorite dessert! It's rich, moist, naturally sweetened and packed with 15 grams of protein per slice." data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-hero.jpg" alt="Chocolate protein cake cut into slices on a table." class="wp-image-143642" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-hero.jpg" srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-hero.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-hero-373x560.jpg 373w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-hero-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-hero-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-hero-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-hero-150x225.jpg 150w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-hero-276x414.jpg 276w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-hero-128x192.jpg 128w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-hero-378x567.jpg 378w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>



<p>This cake is seriously my new obsession &mdash; it&rsquo;s rich, fudgy and perfectly moist all while being packed with protein thanks to the chocolate protein powder and Greek yogurt. And trust me, nobody will even be able to tell that this cake is made healthier. It&rsquo;s guaranteed to be everyone&rsquo;s new favorite dessert! </p>


<div class="wp-block-yoast-seo-table-of-contents yoast-table-of-contents"><h2 id="table-of-contents">Table of Contents</h2><ul><li><a href="#h-why-i-love-this-protein-cake">Why I Love This Protein Cake</a></li><li><a href="#h-ingredients-needed">Ingredients Needed</a></li><li><a href="#h-how-to-make-protein-cake">How to Make Protein Cake</a></li><li><a href="#h-brittany-s-tip">Brittany&rsquo;s Tip</a></li><li><a href="#h-how-to-store-leftovers">How to Store Leftovers</a></li><li><a href="#h-frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions </a></li><li><a href="#h-more-protein-packed-treats-to-try">More Protein-Packed Treats to Try</a></li><li><a href="#wprm-recipe-container-143265">Protein Cake Recipe</a></li></ul></div>

<div class="block-featured-comment has-background has-secondary-background-color"><div class="block-featured-comment__inner">

<p class="has-text-align-center block-featured-comment__quote">&ldquo;This cake was delicious! My husband was skeptical and then proceeded to devour it saying how delicious it was! You would never know this cake is high protein or much healthier than regular cake. I will absolutely be adding this to my regular rotation of treats to make! Even my very picky toddlers ate it for breakfast with yogurt on top!!&rdquo;</p>



<p class="has-text-align-center block-featured-comment__author is-style-interface">&ndash; <a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-1/#comment-26058429890269694" type="link" id="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-1/#comment-26058429890269694">jennifer</a></p>

</div><div class="wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex is-content-justification-center"><a href="#comments" class="wp-element-button is-style-buttton">54 More Reviews</a></div></div>

<div class="block-personal-note cwp-inner cwp-large has-background has-quaternary-background-color">

<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-why-i-love-this-protein-cake">Why I Love This Protein Cake</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image alignright is-resized is-style-rounded"><img width="400" height="400" decoding="async" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20400'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Woman (Brittany Mullins) wearing a white shirt and sipping a green smoothie." style="width:200px;height:200px" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/personal-note-brittany.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/personal-note-brittany.jpg"><noscript><img width="400" height="400" decoding="async" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/personal-note-brittany.jpg" alt="Woman (Brittany Mullins) wearing a white shirt and sipping a green smoothie." style="width:200px;height:200px" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/personal-note-brittany.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Protein-packed</strong>: One slice is packed with 15 grams of protein!</li>



<li><strong>Easy to make</strong>: This recipe comes together quickly with simple, pantry staple ingredients.</li>



<li><strong>Made with simple ingredients</strong>: It&rsquo;s naturally sweetened with maple syrup and made with oat flour, so it feels indulgent without being over the top.</li>



<li><strong>Versatile</strong>:<strong> </strong>Whether it&rsquo;s a post-workout treat, a birthday celebration, or just an everyday dessert, this cake is always a good idea.</li>
</ul>

</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-ingredients-needed">Ingredients Needed</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=189974" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Ingredients measured out to make Protein Cake: vegan chocolate protein powder, oat flour, cocoa powder, almond milk, baking powder, baking soda, salt, eggs, maple syrup, coconut oil, vanilla, Greek yogurt and dark chocolate chips." class="wp-image-189974" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=189974" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new.jpg" alt="Ingredients measured out to make Protein Cake: vegan chocolate protein powder, oat flour, cocoa powder, almond milk, baking powder, baking soda, salt, eggs, maple syrup, coconut oil, vanilla, Greek yogurt and dark chocolate chips." class="wp-image-189974" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new.jpg" srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/protein-cake-ingredients-new-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<p>As I mentioned above, you only need simple, pantry staple ingredients to make this recipe that you probably already have in your kitchen!</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>oat flour</strong> &ndash; we&rsquo;re using oat flour to keep this cake gluten-free. You can use store-bought or make <a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/how-to-make-oat-flour/">homemade oat flour</a> using rolled oats.</li>



<li><strong>chocolate protein powder</strong> &ndash; adds richness, structure, and boosts the protein content of the cake. A plant-based chocolate protein powder works best here.</li>



<li><strong>cocoa powder</strong> &ndash; deepens the chocolate flavor and gives the cake that rich, fudgy vibe. Use unsweetened cocoa powder or raw cacao powder.</li>



<li><strong>maple syrup</strong> &ndash; naturally sweetens the cake without overpowering the chocolate. Be sure to use pure maple syrup, not pancake syrup.</li>



<li><strong>unsweetened almond milk</strong> &ndash; helps keep the cake moist and balances out the dry ingredients. any milk works here, but unsweetened almond milk is my go-to.</li>



<li><strong>full fat plain greek yogurt</strong> &ndash; key for a moist, tender crumb and adds even more protein. I recommend full-fat or 2 percent for the best texture.</li>



<li><strong>eggs</strong> &ndash; binds the ingredients together and adds structure to the cake.</li>



<li><strong>chocolate ganache</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; a simple chocolate topping made with melted chocolate and almond milk. It takes this cake from good to absolutely crave-worthy.</li>
</ul>



<p><em>Find the full ingredient list with measurements in the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/#wprm-recipe-container-143265" type="link" id="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/#wprm-recipe-container-143265">recipe card below</a>.</em></p>



<div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-to-make-protein-cake">How to Make Protein Cake</h2>



<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143647" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="All the dry ingredients used for a protein cake in a large mixing bowl." class="wp-image-143647" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143647" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1.jpg" alt="All the dry ingredients used for a protein cake in a large mixing bowl." class="wp-image-143647" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1.jpg" srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-1-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Mix the dry ingredients. Add the oat flour, protein powder, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda and salt to a medium mixing bowl and stir to combine.</p>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143648" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="All the wet ingredients used for a protein cake in a large mixing bowl." class="wp-image-143648" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143648" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2.jpg" alt="All the wet ingredients used for a protein cake in a large mixing bowl." class="wp-image-143648" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2.jpg" srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-2-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Mix wet ingredients. Add maple syrup, almond milk, yogurt, oil, eggs and vanilla to a large mixing bowl and whisk to combine.</p>
</div>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143649" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Wet and dry ingredients being combined with a silicone spatula in a large mixing bowl." class="wp-image-143649" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143649" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3.jpg" alt="Wet and dry ingredients being combined with a silicone spatula in a large mixing bowl." class="wp-image-143649" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3.jpg" srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-3-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and stir to fully combine, until smooth.</p>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143650" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Batter for a protein cake in a cake pan before being baked." class="wp-image-143650" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143650" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4.jpg" alt="Batter for a protein cake in a cake pan before being baked." class="wp-image-143650" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4.jpg" srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-4-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Pour the batter into the prepared 8&Prime; cake pan and bake at 350F for 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Remove from the oven and let the cake cool completely before frosting.</p>
</div>
</div>



