<p><strong>Step 5:</strong> While the cake is cooling, make the ganache frosting.</p>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143652" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A chocolate frosting is spread on a protein cake with a metal spoon." class="wp-image-143652" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143652" data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6.jpg" alt="A chocolate frosting is spread on a protein cake with a metal spoon." class="wp-image-143652" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6.jpg" srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6-560x373.jpg 560w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-process-6-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<p><strong>Step 6: </strong>Frost the top of the cake, serve, and enjoy!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>


<div class="block-tip cwp-inner has-background has-tertiary-background-color">

<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-left block-tip__title" id="h-brittany-s-tip">Brittany&rsquo;s Tip</h2>



<p>This cake bakes best with a plant-based chocolate protein powder. I tested it with <a href="https://bit.ly/3UN0214" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored nofollow">Sun Warrior</a> and <a href="https://nuzest-usa.com/?rfsn=4039758.ceb810" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored nofollow">Nuzest</a> and both worked really well. I don&rsquo;t recommend using whey protein here, as it tends to absorb too much liquid and can make the cake dry and dense.</p>



<p>If you use Nuzest, you can use code <em>eatingbirdfood</em> for 15% off your order. </p>

</div></div>



