<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143654" data-pin-description="This delicious chocolate protein cake is guaranteed to be your new favorite dessert! It's rich, moist, naturally sweetened and packed with 15 grams of protein per slice." data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A small bite-sized portion taken from a slice of chocolate protein cake with a fork." class="wp-image-143654" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-373x560.jpg 373w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-150x225.jpg 150w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-276x414.jpg 276w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-128x192.jpg 128w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-378x567.jpg 378w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" data-pin-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?tp_image_id=143654" data-pin-description="This delicious chocolate protein cake is guaranteed to be your new favorite dessert! It's rich, moist, naturally sweetened and packed with 15 grams of protein per slice." data-pin-title="Protein Cake" src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork.jpg" alt="A small bite-sized portion taken from a slice of chocolate protein cake with a fork." class="wp-image-143654" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="This rich, fudgy chocolate protein cake is naturally sweetened and made with simple ingredients like Greek yogurt, oat flour, and protein powder. Each slice packs 15 grams of protein, but tastes just like a classic chocolate cake." data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Protein Cake" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork.jpg" srcset="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork.jpg 1200w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-373x560.jpg 373w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-150x225.jpg 150w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-276x414.jpg 276w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-128x192.jpg 128w, https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/protein-cake-with-fork-378x567.jpg 378w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-to-store-leftovers">How to Store Leftovers</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Room temperature:</strong> Store the cake in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 2 days. This works best if you plan to enjoy it quickly and want to keep the texture soft and moist.</li>



<li><strong>Refrigerator:</strong> For longer storage, keep the cake covered in the fridge for up to 5 days. I like letting a slice sit out for a few minutes before eating so it softens back up.</li>



<li><strong>Freezing:</strong> You can freeze the unfrosted cake for up to 3 months. Wrap it tightly in plastic wrap, then foil. Thaw overnight in the refrigerator before frosting and serving.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions </h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1707450077265"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Can I use a different frosting?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Absolutely! I love the chocolate ganache topping, but feel free to use your favorite frosting for this cake. For more of a real deal frosting try this <a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/vanilla-buttercream-frosting/">vanilla buttercream frosting</a> or <a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/strawberry-buttercream-frosting/">strawberry buttercream frosting</a>. This <a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/greek-yogurt-frosting/">peanut butter yogurt frosting</a> or <a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/healthy-chocolate-frosting/">healthy chocolate frosting</a> would also be delicious!</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1772064762249"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Why is my protein cake dry?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Protein cakes can turn out dry if too much protein powder or flour is used. Measuring the oat flour correctly and using Greek yogurt are key for keeping this cake moist and tender.</p> </div> </div>


