			<h2 class="comments-title">55 Comments</h2>
				<ol class="comment-list">
					<li id="comment-26058429890326170" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890326170" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Rsaaa</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890326170"><time datetime="2026-05-07T22:01:08-04:00">May 7, 2026 at 10:01 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
Does this call for 1 cup or 1 scoop of protein powder? Also can i mix half chocolate half vanilla bean powder if i don’t have enough chocolate protein? Thank you!</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890326170" data-commentid="26058429890326170" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890326170" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Rsaaa" aria-label="Reply to Rsaaa">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		<ol class="children">
		<li id="comment-26058429890326242" class="comment byuser comment-author-alex odd alt depth-2 staff">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890326242" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Brittany Mullins</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890326242"><time datetime="2026-05-10T20:14:29-04:00">May 10, 2026 at 8:14 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Great question! It’s 1 scoop of protein powder, not 1 cup. And yes, you can definitely do half chocolate and half vanilla protein powder if that’s what you have on hand. Hope you enjoy it!</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890326242" data-commentid="26058429890326242" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890326242" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Brittany Mullins" aria-label="Reply to Brittany Mullins">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-26058429890324689" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890324689" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Labubu</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890324689"><time datetime="2026-04-05T08:18:40-04:00">April 5, 2026 at 8:18 am</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
Thank you so much, love this recipe.<br />
Also thank you for putting the measurements under each step, that&#8217;s very thoughtful.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890324689" data-commentid="26058429890324689" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890324689" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Labubu" aria-label="Reply to Labubu">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		<ol class="children">
		<li id="comment-26058429890324723" class="comment byuser comment-author-alex odd alt depth-2 staff">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890324723" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Brittany Mullins</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890324723"><time datetime="2026-04-05T22:48:30-04:00">April 5, 2026 at 10:48 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>So glad you loved this recipe! I’m happy the measurements in each step were helpful, that’s always my goal. Thanks for making the recipe and for coming back to leave a review. It means the world to me!</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890324723" data-commentid="26058429890324723" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890324723" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Brittany Mullins" aria-label="Reply to Brittany Mullins">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-26058429890322469" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890322469" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">rose</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890322469"><time datetime="2026-02-22T11:45:01-05:00">February 22, 2026 at 11:45 am</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Ganache is usually made with butter/milk/chocolate or whipping cream/chocolate.  How does using the almond milk only taste&#8230;would like to know before I try!</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890322469" data-commentid="26058429890322469" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890322469" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to rose" aria-label="Reply to rose">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		<ol class="children">
		<li id="comment-26058429890322508" class="comment byuser comment-author-alex odd alt depth-2 staff">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890322508" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Brittany Mullins</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890322508"><time datetime="2026-02-23T13:14:06-05:00">February 23, 2026 at 1:14 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Great question! The almond milk version is still rich and chocolatey, just a bit lighter than a traditional cream-based ganache. It sets up nicely once the cake cools and pairs really well with the cake without feeling heavy.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890322508" data-commentid="26058429890322508" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890322508" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Brittany Mullins" aria-label="Reply to Brittany Mullins">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-26058429890322301" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890322301" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Brittany</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890322301"><time datetime="2026-02-19T12:06:31-05:00">February 19, 2026 at 12:06 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
Delicious. Made this for my husband’s birthday and we all loved it. Thanks again for another great recipe!</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890322301" data-commentid="26058429890322301" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890322301" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Brittany" aria-label="Reply to Brittany">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-26058429890321906" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890321906" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Jake</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890321906"><time datetime="2026-02-10T14:01:42-05:00">February 10, 2026 at 2:01 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Would you recommend just using protein powder without a sweetener? I&#8217;m planning on using the Orgain Vanilla Bean plant protein powder, which already has stevia in it. It&#8217;s pretty sweet to me. I&#8217;ll compensate the chocolate flavor with an extra 1/4 cup of cocoa powder. I just wonder if it&#8217;d be sweet enough. I often make mug cakes with just the Orgain protein powder and it tends to be sweet enough for me.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890321906" data-commentid="26058429890321906" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890321906" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jake" aria-label="Reply to Jake">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		<ol class="children">
		<li id="comment-26058429890321930" class="comment byuser comment-author-alex even depth-2 staff">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890321930" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Brittany Mullins</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890321930"><time datetime="2026-02-10T21:18:32-05:00">February 10, 2026 at 9:18 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Great question, Jake! Since the maple syrup is doing most of the sweetening here, I wouldn’t recommend removing it completely, but you could try reducing it if your protein powder is already quite sweet and adjust to taste.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890321930" data-commentid="26058429890321930" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890321930" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Brittany Mullins" aria-label="Reply to Brittany Mullins">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-26058429890321702" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890321702" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Keely</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890321702"><time datetime="2026-02-05T15:24:21-05:00">February 5, 2026 at 3:24 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
Delicious! Made this for my husbands birthday, will definitely make again!</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890321702" data-commentid="26058429890321702" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890321702" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Keely" aria-label="Reply to Keely">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		<ol class="children">
		<li id="comment-26058429890321717" class="comment byuser comment-author-alex even depth-2 staff">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890321717" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Brittany Mullins</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890321717"><time datetime="2026-02-05T18:15:34-05:00">February 5, 2026 at 6:15 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>So glad this recipe was a hit, Keely! I love that you made it for your husband’s birthday and that it’s already on your make-again list. Thanks so much for making it and for coming back to leave a review.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890321717" data-commentid="26058429890321717" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890321717" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Brittany Mullins" aria-label="Reply to Brittany Mullins">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-26058429890321630" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890321630" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Gail</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890321630"><time datetime="2026-02-03T15:37:55-05:00">February 3, 2026 at 3:37 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Can I use 2% greek yogurt??</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890321630" data-commentid="26058429890321630" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890321630" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Gail" aria-label="Reply to Gail">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		<ol class="children">
		<li id="comment-26058429890321656" class="comment byuser comment-author-alex even depth-2 staff">
			<article id="div-comment-26058429890321656" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Brittany Mullins</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/comment-page-3/#comment-26058429890321656"><time datetime="2026-02-04T11:45:21-05:00">February 4, 2026 at 11:45 am</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I haven’t tested this recipe with 2% yogurt, but it will likely work. Just keep in mind the cake may be a bit less moist than if you use full-fat.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a  class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-26058429890321656" data-commentid="26058429890321656" data-postid="143263" data-belowelement="div-comment-26058429890321656" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Brittany Mullins" aria-label="Reply to Brittany Mullins">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		</ol><!-- .comment-list -->
		<p class="wp-block-button"><a class="load-more-comments wp-block-button__link" href="https://www.eatingbirdfood.com/protein-cake/?load_all_comments=1#comments">See More Comments</a></p>
</div><!-- #comments -->
